The paper deals with the study of structural properties of backdoors in Reiter's propositional default logic, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also considers the problems of backdoor detection and evaluation, which are related to computational complexity and algorithms, respectively. Therefore, the paper could also be classified under categories such as cs.LO (logic in computer science), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CC (computational complexity), and cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
